WEBVTT

00:01.540 --> 00:08.080
♪♪

00:08.080 --> 00:10.250
Did you fold
all of this?
Yep.

00:10.250 --> 00:12.120
[ Chuckles ]
It's dirty, but thank you.

00:12.120 --> 00:13.960
Ugh. There were so many
undies in it.

00:13.960 --> 00:15.000
Ugh.

00:17.290 --> 00:18.790
You seem relaxed.

00:18.790 --> 00:20.250
Must be feeling good
about your presentation

00:20.250 --> 00:22.170
for the Spring Gala.
It's no biggie.

00:22.170 --> 00:23.460
I just have to pitch
them the theme.

00:23.460 --> 00:24.460
Which is?

00:24.460 --> 00:26.460
Um...

00:26.460 --> 00:27.960
The presentation is today
and you don't have a theme?

00:27.960 --> 00:29.040
Of course I do.

00:29.040 --> 00:30.540
[ Scoffs ]

00:30.540 --> 00:31.710
Water...

00:31.710 --> 00:33.250
blankets...

00:33.250 --> 00:34.500
Are you just looking
around the kitchen,

00:34.500 --> 00:35.620
calling out objects.

00:35.620 --> 00:36.380
No.

00:38.040 --> 00:39.540
Dirt.

00:39.540 --> 00:41.460
Sand.

00:41.460 --> 00:43.330
Beach blanket bingo!

00:43.330 --> 00:44.580
In your face!

00:44.580 --> 00:46.580
Why is it in my face?
Okay, picture this.

00:46.580 --> 00:48.790
Everyone on
giant beach towels,

00:48.790 --> 00:51.080
we have a picnic, and we drink
that stupid pink wine.

00:51.080 --> 00:52.580
Maybe steel drums...

00:52.580 --> 00:54.290
Rinka-tink-tink-tink.

00:54.290 --> 00:55.790
Tink.

00:55.790 --> 00:57.290
Huh. That's actually
a good idea, honey.

00:58.380 --> 01:00.710
That's actually
a terrible idea, honey.

01:00.710 --> 01:03.920
The Spring Gala is a fundraiser,
not a hoedown.

01:03.920 --> 01:06.120
The whole thing is about
raising money.

01:06.120 --> 01:08.170
You want people to
open their pockets.

01:09.790 --> 01:11.790
You can take the girl
out of Florida...

01:11.790 --> 01:13.380
Oh, great.
I was hoping

01:13.380 --> 01:15.330
for a smart-ass
13 year old's opinion.

01:15.330 --> 01:16.920
At your service.

01:16.920 --> 01:19.380
You need a theme to
get people spending.

01:19.380 --> 01:22.790
Something that says "class,"
"decadence," "money."

01:22.790 --> 01:24.420
Mine will have class.

01:24.420 --> 01:27.580
I'm gonna rename the bathrooms
"cabanas."

01:27.580 --> 01:28.620
Stop.

01:28.620 --> 01:30.080
It needs to be opulent.

01:30.080 --> 01:33.420
Like a "Great Gatsby" party.
Or, uh, Bollywood.

01:33.420 --> 01:34.920
Nothing says
"Write a big check"

01:34.920 --> 01:36.580
like an elephant
cloaked in velvet,

01:36.580 --> 01:39.330
or a one-twelfth scale Taj Mahal
made out of white chocolate.

01:39.330 --> 01:40.790
You know what's easier?

01:40.790 --> 01:42.380
Buying a bunch
of blankets.

01:42.380 --> 01:43.540
I'm doing this my way.

01:43.540 --> 01:44.790
But --
[ Cellphone rings ]

01:44.790 --> 01:46.380
Oh, my God.

01:46.380 --> 01:48.040
Yeah, blankets.
Can't miss.

01:48.040 --> 01:50.330
I have the perfect theme
for your Gala, Mama.

01:50.330 --> 01:52.170
"Let's get a dog!"

01:52.170 --> 01:53.420
In case I haven't
been clear,

01:53.420 --> 01:56.040
we are never, ever
getting a dog, ever.

01:56.040 --> 01:57.750
It's like having another kid,
except it sheds

01:57.750 --> 01:59.750
and digs tampons
out of the trash.

01:59.750 --> 02:01.080
Fine.

02:01.080 --> 02:02.880
Thanks for the backup,
Franklin.

02:02.880 --> 02:04.960
Where was that
"Great thinking, Anna-Kat"

02:04.960 --> 02:06.460
that we talked about?

02:06.460 --> 02:08.170
What's a tampon?

02:08.170 --> 02:10.960
I'm not Google,
Franklin.

02:10.960 --> 02:12.790
Hey, guys.
My boyfriend's here.

02:12.790 --> 02:14.460
Please don't
embarrass me.
Hey, Eyo.

02:14.460 --> 02:16.960
♪ Eyoooooo,
Eyooooo ♪

02:16.960 --> 02:18.210
[ Chuckles ]
Or just ignore me.

02:18.210 --> 02:20.330
Quite a set of pipes,
Mr. Otto!

02:20.330 --> 02:21.960
[ Chuckles ]
What are you guys up to?

02:21.960 --> 02:23.880
Taylor and I are gonna
do some English homework.

02:23.880 --> 02:25.250
Great.
And, Taylor, remember,

02:25.250 --> 02:26.500
don't copy
word-for-word.

02:26.500 --> 02:28.000
Mix it up
a little bit.

02:28.000 --> 02:29.540
[ Scoffs ]
I almost killed myself

02:29.540 --> 02:31.040
on that big box
by the door!

02:31.040 --> 02:32.080
[ Gasps ]
It's here!

02:32.080 --> 02:33.500
Eyo, give me a hand.

02:33.500 --> 02:34.960
Dad, get friends.

02:34.960 --> 02:36.880
She's joking. I've got,
like, so many friends.

02:40.000 --> 02:41.670
I thought
I smelled kale.

02:41.670 --> 02:42.710
What do you want,
Tara?

02:42.710 --> 02:43.790
Just making sure
everything's safe

02:43.790 --> 02:45.750
in this lawless house.

02:45.750 --> 02:47.830
I trust you have
a vegan lunch option for Eyo.

02:47.830 --> 02:50.540
We're vegan now.
Tara, you're already
the worst.

02:50.540 --> 02:51.830
Stop trying so hard.

02:51.830 --> 02:54.000
Okay, coming through.

02:54.000 --> 02:55.670
Oh.

02:55.670 --> 02:56.670
Here we go.

02:56.670 --> 02:57.710
[ Stool clatters ]
Oh!

02:57.710 --> 02:59.120
Okay, good.
That needed to be broken.

03:00.330 --> 03:01.710
So did the piano.

03:01.710 --> 03:02.620
And your shoe.

03:02.620 --> 03:04.420
Your shoe just fell off.

03:04.420 --> 03:06.420
And if you could dent the door
on your way out,

03:06.420 --> 03:07.330
that'd be great.

03:07.330 --> 03:08.500
[ Greg chuckles ]

03:08.500 --> 03:09.620
Yeah, one second.

03:09.620 --> 03:10.750
Who are you
talking to?

03:10.750 --> 03:11.620
It's Nunya.

03:11.620 --> 03:13.120
Who's that?

03:13.120 --> 03:14.920
Nunya business.
[none of your]

03:14.920 --> 03:16.040
One of these days,
I'm gonna realize

03:16.040 --> 03:17.920
that "nunya"
isn't a person.

03:17.920 --> 03:20.830
So, have you picked out your
theme yet for the Spring Gala?

03:20.830 --> 03:22.250
Because I have
a suggestion.

03:22.250 --> 03:25.330
Call it, "Katie" colon
"The Great Failure" comma

03:25.330 --> 03:28.120
"Everyone Saw it Coming"
dash dash "She Sucks."

03:28.120 --> 03:29.710
I got it covered,
Tara.

03:29.710 --> 03:31.330
I'm thinking
"Beef Jerky,"

03:31.330 --> 03:35.540
"The Final Frontier"
or "Mmm, Meat."

03:35.540 --> 03:36.830
I'm leaving.

03:36.830 --> 03:39.080
Call or text
or e-mail

03:39.080 --> 03:41.620
or post on Facebook
if Eyo needs anything.

03:41.620 --> 03:45.710
Here's his EpiPen
and some toilet seat covers.

03:45.710 --> 03:48.420
You send toilet seat covers
with him everywhere he goes?

03:48.420 --> 03:49.500
No.

03:51.120 --> 03:53.670
Good slam, Tara.
Here's mine.

03:53.670 --> 03:55.920
♪♪

04:05.080 --> 04:06.540
While I've got you here,
I wonder if you might

04:06.540 --> 04:08.710
put in a good word
with Taylor about college.

04:08.710 --> 04:10.580
Sure. Probably would
have come up anyway.

04:10.580 --> 04:11.790
School's the best!

04:11.790 --> 04:13.750
Thanks. Great talk.

04:13.750 --> 04:16.250
Sorry we're standing
closer than I expected.

04:16.250 --> 04:18.040
Hi, Mrs. Otto.
How are you?

04:18.040 --> 04:19.710
Saw you
three minutes ago.

04:19.710 --> 04:22.960
Hey, you with the box,
is this our next fight?

04:22.960 --> 04:25.170
You're gonna love it.
It's a roasting box.

04:25.170 --> 04:26.250
You can cook a whole pig
in here.

04:26.250 --> 04:28.330
I saw one on
Anthony Bourdain's show.

04:28.330 --> 04:30.000
He was in Guatemala
cooking with the locals.

04:30.000 --> 04:31.290
He was wearing
a tank top.

04:31.290 --> 04:32.460
Oh, Greg,
would you please,

04:32.460 --> 04:34.830
for me, watch something
with dragons?

04:34.830 --> 04:36.170
Once I fire this up,
you're gonna realize

04:36.170 --> 04:38.040
we need a Caja China
roasting box.

04:38.040 --> 04:41.290
No. I need to change
our Amazon password.
Think about it.

04:41.290 --> 04:43.250
We could finally have a barbecue
for all our friends.

04:43.250 --> 04:44.210
So...

04:44.210 --> 04:46.000
Angela and Doris?

04:46.000 --> 04:48.580
How long does it take
to cook a pig?
Just half a day.

04:48.580 --> 04:50.460
As long as I constantly
monitor it, stoke the coals,

04:50.460 --> 04:52.460
and make sure the temperature
remains exactly correct.

04:52.460 --> 04:53.710
We both know that this
is going to end

04:53.710 --> 04:55.620
with Anna-Kat forcing us
to have a funeral

04:55.620 --> 04:57.620
for a partially-cooked
pig carcass,

04:57.620 --> 04:59.460
and I can't fit into
my funeral dress right now.

04:59.460 --> 05:00.670
I don't need this,
Greg.
Yeah, but --

05:00.670 --> 05:02.170
I'm afraid I have
to shut this down.

05:02.170 --> 05:04.040
But --
I'm shutting it down.

05:04.040 --> 05:05.500
You're probably right.

05:05.500 --> 05:07.120
I don't really have the arms
for a tank top anyway.

05:09.580 --> 05:12.330
"No, honey, you definitely
have the arms for a tank top."

05:12.330 --> 05:14.080
Well, I think
it could be fun.

05:14.080 --> 05:15.580
It's a bad idea,
Franklin.

05:15.580 --> 05:17.960
It's a hard "no."
Discussion's over.

05:17.960 --> 05:19.040
[ Sighs ]
But --

05:19.040 --> 05:20.420
I said over.

05:22.120 --> 05:23.920
I guess you're right.

05:23.920 --> 05:25.880
Anna-Kat, can we talk
to you in my office?

05:25.880 --> 05:27.250
Uh-oh.

05:27.250 --> 05:28.880
Franklin, this might
be a while.

05:28.880 --> 05:30.790
If you still need
to go number two,

05:30.790 --> 05:31.750
here's your window.

05:34.750 --> 05:36.000
Your parents like me?

05:36.000 --> 05:37.460
Let's see who you've
been talking to.
Hey!

05:37.460 --> 05:39.080
[ Gasps ]
Alice McCarthy?!

05:39.080 --> 05:40.120
I thought
she dumped you!

05:40.120 --> 05:42.500
Are you crazy?

05:42.500 --> 05:43.790
Alice McCarthy?

05:43.790 --> 05:45.080
Yeah, I thought he
stopped picking up

05:45.080 --> 05:46.710
what she was putting down.

05:46.710 --> 05:47.670
Did I say that right?

05:47.670 --> 05:49.710
Yeah.

05:49.710 --> 05:52.170
Do I have to be
here for this?
Sit.

05:52.170 --> 05:54.040
You were very rude
to Franklin.

05:54.040 --> 05:55.710
But I didn't
like his idea.

05:55.710 --> 05:58.000
You can't shut
people down like that.

05:58.000 --> 05:59.250
Where did you
get that from?

06:01.250 --> 06:02.460
Why are you
looking at me?

06:02.460 --> 06:04.120
If you keep rejecting
people's ideas,

06:04.120 --> 06:05.580
they won't
be your friend.

06:05.580 --> 06:07.380
That's true, honey.
It's important that we support

06:07.380 --> 06:09.620
the people
we care about. Okay?

06:09.620 --> 06:11.210
Okay.
So, for instance,

06:11.210 --> 06:12.540
if Franklin loved
Anthony Bourdain

06:12.540 --> 06:13.750
and wanted to throw
a pig roast...

06:13.750 --> 06:15.790
Oh, that's why you
were looking at me.

06:15.790 --> 06:17.040
...what would you
say to him?

06:17.040 --> 06:18.750
I'd say,
"Weird, Franklin,

06:18.750 --> 06:20.580
but it sounds like
a great idea"?

06:20.580 --> 06:22.920
Right. And what would
you say, Katie?

06:22.920 --> 06:25.420
I would be forced to say,

06:25.420 --> 06:27.790
"That sounds like
a great idea," too.

06:27.790 --> 06:29.080
So, it's settled.
We're gonna have a barbecue

06:29.080 --> 06:30.380
for all our friends!

06:30.380 --> 06:31.210
So...

06:31.210 --> 06:32.250
Angela and Doris?

06:39.580 --> 06:41.540
You know, you can roast
18 whole chickens in here?

06:41.540 --> 06:43.420
18? Oh, thank God.

06:43.420 --> 06:44.790
I was worried what would
happen if we had to cook

06:44.790 --> 06:46.330
17 more than usual.

06:46.330 --> 06:47.380
You know, Katie,

06:47.380 --> 06:49.040
this is where Anna-Kat
gets it from.

06:49.040 --> 06:50.750
She sees you shutting down
my ideas

06:50.750 --> 06:53.000
and does the same thing
to poor, defenseless Franklin.

06:53.000 --> 06:56.460
Yeah, but she also
has my winning smile.

06:56.460 --> 06:58.000
Ding.
I'm serious.

06:58.000 --> 07:00.290
You need to just say "okay" to
me sometimes, like I do for you.

07:00.290 --> 07:02.380
I say "okay" to you
all the time.

07:02.380 --> 07:04.210
Yeah, but that's because
my ideas are always good.

07:04.210 --> 07:05.380
Really?

07:05.380 --> 07:06.790
Pull that thing off
the steering wheel.

07:06.790 --> 07:07.460
It's driving me crazy.

07:07.460 --> 07:09.620
Okay.

07:09.620 --> 07:10.880
[ Laughs ]

07:10.880 --> 07:12.120
It wasn't funny.

07:12.120 --> 07:13.750
I know. I know.

07:13.750 --> 07:15.830
It was just the look on
your face when it hit you.

07:15.830 --> 07:19.620
[ Snickers ]
I'm sorry.

07:19.620 --> 07:21.790
I'm just saying it wouldn't
hurt if, once in a while,

07:21.790 --> 07:24.080
you supported me the way
that I support you.

07:24.080 --> 07:26.880
Fine, I'll okay this,
but --
No. No.

07:26.880 --> 07:29.170
No "Okay, buts."
Just, "Okay."

07:29.170 --> 07:31.380
Ohh-kaaay.
You know what?

07:31.380 --> 07:32.670
You can't say it like that.
Not sing-songy.

07:32.670 --> 07:34.040
Sorry.
This is new to me.

07:34.040 --> 07:36.620
It's very hard to suppress
my natural critical instincts.

07:36.620 --> 07:38.460
But fine.

07:38.460 --> 07:40.250
I'm saying...

07:40.250 --> 07:41.580
okay.

07:41.580 --> 07:43.460
Thank you.

07:43.460 --> 07:45.170
Now, do you want to practice
your presentation

07:45.170 --> 07:47.620
for the Spring Gala?
Eh. I'll just wing it.

07:47.620 --> 07:49.420
The school takes these
events very seriously.

07:49.420 --> 07:51.330
Maybe winging it
isn't the best idea.

07:51.330 --> 07:53.120
Hey, if I can't second-guess
your pig coffin,

07:53.120 --> 07:55.790
there's no way you're allowed
to second-guess me on this.

07:55.790 --> 07:59.250
Ohh-kaaay.

07:59.250 --> 08:01.210
Yeah, I can see
how that's annoying.

08:01.210 --> 08:02.620
Mm.

08:02.620 --> 08:05.580
♪♪

08:05.580 --> 08:07.960
But it's not so easy
being supportive of him.

08:07.960 --> 08:10.080
And I don't have a good
supportive smile.

08:10.080 --> 08:11.250
It looks like there's
a gun to my head

08:11.250 --> 08:12.580
and I'm trying to
convince the police

08:12.580 --> 08:14.250
that there's not
an intruder inside.

08:14.250 --> 08:16.170
[ Laughing ]

08:16.170 --> 08:18.330
What you need
is one of these.

08:18.330 --> 08:19.790
It's a complaint
bracelet.

08:19.790 --> 08:21.580
I read about it
in Good Housekeeping.

08:21.580 --> 08:22.920
Every time you want to
scream at your husband

08:22.920 --> 08:25.500
for some boneheaded idea...

08:25.500 --> 08:26.420
...you snap it...

08:26.420 --> 08:27.710
so you don't snap
at him for buying

08:27.710 --> 08:30.210
thousands of dollars
of movie memorabilia.

08:30.210 --> 08:32.710
[ Whimsical music plays ]

08:32.710 --> 08:38.000
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

08:38.000 --> 08:39.500
[ Sighs ]

08:39.500 --> 08:40.920
Does that work?

08:40.920 --> 08:42.670
He's a pain in the ass
and I'm a living nightmare --

08:42.670 --> 08:43.880
still married!

08:43.880 --> 08:45.120
[ Chuckles ]
I love it.

08:45.120 --> 08:47.000
I gotta get one.
Oh, take mine.

08:47.000 --> 08:48.620
I get a new shipment
every week.

08:48.620 --> 08:51.290
Mm. Maybe it'll also help you
deal with the Spring Gala.

08:51.290 --> 08:52.880
I am not one of
those uptight moms.

08:52.880 --> 08:54.670
It is a party,
and it's six months away.

08:54.670 --> 08:56.580
I'm not gonna let these people
drive me crazy.

08:56.580 --> 08:58.500
That's what last year's
Spring Gala chairwoman,

08:58.500 --> 08:59.670
Stacy Clouser, said.

08:59.670 --> 09:00.960
Then she had a nervous
breakdown,

09:00.960 --> 09:02.540
had to move in
with her parents

09:02.540 --> 09:05.120
and now isn't allowed
to have stuffed animals.

09:05.120 --> 09:06.790
Because she eats them.

09:06.790 --> 09:08.500
That's not gonna
happen to me.

09:08.500 --> 09:10.710
Okay, and now you're
being annoying.

09:10.710 --> 09:12.460
Which reminds me of Greg.

09:12.460 --> 09:13.920
Which reminds me...

09:13.920 --> 09:15.670
You're the guests of honor
at Greg's barbecue.

09:15.670 --> 09:17.170
And by "honor"

09:17.170 --> 09:18.880
I mean you're
the only guests.
[ Chuckles ]

09:22.670 --> 09:24.960
All right, it's all set.
Now I just need the pig.

09:24.960 --> 09:28.540
Okay, sounds great.

09:28.540 --> 09:31.460
Why are you allowing this?
What does he have on you?

09:31.460 --> 09:33.580
Your dad asked if we
could throw a barbecue,

09:33.580 --> 09:36.000
and I said...okay.

09:36.000 --> 09:37.830
See? It's important
to be supportive

09:37.830 --> 09:39.080
of your friends' ideas.

09:40.580 --> 09:43.290
Then we should be supportive
of my idea to get a dog.

09:43.290 --> 09:45.000
I'm not your friend.
I'm your mother.

09:45.000 --> 09:46.710
We'll be friends when
you're old enough to drink.

09:46.710 --> 09:47.750
[ Cellphone rings ]

09:47.750 --> 09:49.620
Ooh, Alice.
I got to take this.

09:49.620 --> 09:50.830
Go for Oliver.

09:50.830 --> 09:52.080
Unh-unh!

09:54.210 --> 09:56.210
What have you done?!
She's bad news.

09:56.210 --> 09:57.750
She broke your heart
when she chose that

09:57.750 --> 09:59.380
hunky Kurt Brockwell
over you.

09:59.380 --> 10:00.750
Kurt Brockwell's 14.

10:00.750 --> 10:01.790
Might be 15 now.

10:01.790 --> 10:03.290
We all know
what she did.

10:03.290 --> 10:05.460
But she's the perfect balance
of hot and rich.

10:05.460 --> 10:07.960
If she wants me back,
I'm crawling back!

10:07.960 --> 10:09.120
Dad, help me
out here.

10:09.120 --> 10:11.790
Sorry, buddy,
not this time.

10:11.790 --> 10:14.670
We Otto men have a long, proud
history of being wusses

10:14.670 --> 10:17.040
and rolling over for our women,
but that ends now.

10:17.040 --> 10:19.580
It does?
Yes. Today
we make a stand.

10:19.580 --> 10:21.670
We roast pigs in boxes, even
though it's been questioned

10:21.670 --> 10:22.920
every step of the way.

10:22.920 --> 10:24.170
And we don't take calls
from girls

10:24.170 --> 10:25.250
who've broken
our hearts --

10:25.250 --> 10:26.790
Can we let the call
go to voicemail

10:26.790 --> 10:29.000
and listen to their sweet
voices whenever we want?

10:29.000 --> 10:31.330
No. That's creepy.

10:31.330 --> 10:33.170
It's time for the Otto men
to break

10:33.170 --> 10:34.460
the wuss chains
and man up!

10:34.460 --> 10:36.250
Are you with me?!

10:36.250 --> 10:38.330
I'm with you!
Let's go get that pig!

10:38.330 --> 10:39.960
Great. Now grab
your sweater!

10:39.960 --> 10:42.040
Yes! It gets breezy
in the late afternoon!

10:42.040 --> 10:47.250
♪♪

10:50.420 --> 10:51.710
High school's great,

10:51.710 --> 10:53.250
but I can't wait
to get to college.

10:53.250 --> 10:54.920
You know, you get
to be on your own --

10:54.920 --> 10:56.380
Did my dad
put you up to this?

10:56.380 --> 10:59.250
Well, yeah,
but he's not wrong.

10:59.250 --> 11:00.540
College is where you
get to focus on

11:00.540 --> 11:01.880
what you're
passionate about.

11:01.880 --> 11:04.380
For me, it's about becoming
an anesthesiologist.

11:04.380 --> 11:07.540
That's your passion?
To be an anesthesiologist?

11:07.540 --> 11:09.920
That and finally
trying bologna.

11:09.920 --> 11:13.000
Anesthesiology is what
your mom wants you to do.

11:13.000 --> 11:16.210
You should do something
that you care about.

11:16.210 --> 11:19.250
Like this! You're always
drawing these cartoons.

11:19.250 --> 11:20.920
They're not cartoons.
It's called manga.

11:20.920 --> 11:22.460
It's a Japanese form
of comic books.

11:22.460 --> 11:24.920
Okay, whatever it's called,
you clearly love it.

11:24.920 --> 11:27.290
This is what you should do
with your life.

11:27.290 --> 11:28.620
[ Giggles ]

11:28.620 --> 11:30.080
Is this a cat
wearing a bra?

11:30.080 --> 11:31.920
Yeah, he solves
crimes.

11:31.920 --> 11:40.250
♪♪

11:40.250 --> 11:42.040
Hey.

11:42.040 --> 11:43.710
Greg Otto.

11:43.710 --> 11:44.960
I'm here to pick up
the pig we ordered

11:44.960 --> 11:47.750
so we can cook it like,
you know...men.

11:47.750 --> 11:49.080
I got you all set up.

11:49.080 --> 11:50.620
[ Cellphone rings ]

11:50.620 --> 11:52.670
One second.

11:52.670 --> 11:55.040
Hey, Alice.

11:55.040 --> 11:56.880
No, I-I don't think
I can go on

11:56.880 --> 11:59.330
your parents' yacht
this weekend.

11:59.330 --> 12:00.750
I got another call.
Gotta go.

12:02.290 --> 12:04.040
I didn't have
another call.

12:04.040 --> 12:07.330
You just earned yourself
a fat stack of man cards.

12:07.330 --> 12:08.500
[ Laughs ]

12:08.500 --> 12:10.210
You're gonna
feed seven?
Yeah.

12:10.210 --> 12:13.210
I'd suggest
Louise or R.J.

12:13.210 --> 12:14.790
Uh...

12:14.790 --> 12:16.420
when I ordered
the pig online,

12:16.420 --> 12:18.250
I was under the impression
it wouldn't be so...

12:18.250 --> 12:19.540
alive.

12:19.540 --> 12:22.330
Well, we only sell
live pigs.

12:22.330 --> 12:24.380
Now, what you can do is take it
to the butcher down the road.

12:24.380 --> 12:25.830
He'll slaughter,
gut, and dress

12:25.830 --> 12:27.670
any one of these
little guys for you.

12:27.670 --> 12:29.920
Or you can do it
yourself.

12:29.920 --> 12:30.790
Is there a problem?

12:30.790 --> 12:33.000
No, no, no.
It's no problem.

12:33.000 --> 12:34.540
I made an enormous deal
about a pig roast,

12:34.540 --> 12:36.710
so we are roasting a pig.

12:36.710 --> 12:39.380
R.J., if you have any
female spider friends,

12:39.380 --> 12:41.790
they have about 5 minutes
to work their magic.

12:41.790 --> 12:46.670
♪♪

12:46.670 --> 12:48.040
How's it going
out here?

12:48.040 --> 12:49.500
I just have to cook it
another couple of hours

12:49.500 --> 12:50.580
and then I get
to flip it!

12:50.580 --> 12:52.420
It's going better
than I expected.

12:52.420 --> 12:54.380
All of our friends are going
to be so impressed.

12:54.380 --> 12:55.710
So Angela and Doris?

12:55.710 --> 12:57.040
Yeah.

13:01.620 --> 13:03.670
We're going to need
more chocolate syrup.

13:03.670 --> 13:04.580
A lot more.

13:06.170 --> 13:08.580
We could be in Mexico
in 17 hours.

13:08.580 --> 13:10.580
How do you know --
I just know, Greg.

13:10.580 --> 13:13.830
♪♪

13:13.830 --> 13:15.880
What in the world
are you two doing?!

13:15.880 --> 13:18.830
Anna-Kat, what
has gotten into you?

13:18.830 --> 13:20.620
I'm just doing what
you told me to do.

13:20.620 --> 13:23.170
Yeah, honey, "No TV until
you destroy your room."

13:23.170 --> 13:24.580
Pretty sure I never
said that.

13:24.580 --> 13:26.210
Franklin wanted
to turn my room

13:26.210 --> 13:28.210
into Willy Wonka's
Chocolate Factory.

13:28.210 --> 13:30.500
I told him it was stupid,
but then you said

13:30.500 --> 13:32.460
I should say, "Okay."

13:32.460 --> 13:33.580
So here we are.

13:33.580 --> 13:35.460
Anna-Kat, you should've
stopped him.

13:35.460 --> 13:37.710
Because, even though
we need to be supported...

13:37.710 --> 13:41.580
...sometimes boys have ideas
that need to be shut down.

13:41.580 --> 13:45.380
We're not talking about
Franklin anymore, are we?

13:45.380 --> 13:46.620
[ R.J. oinks ]

13:48.580 --> 13:49.790
Was that our dinner?

13:49.790 --> 13:51.500
His name is R.J.

13:56.920 --> 13:58.080
Who's a good boy?
You're a good boy.

13:58.080 --> 13:59.290
You're a good boy. Get down.
Get down. Get down.

13:59.290 --> 14:00.790
This is why
I don't say "Okay."

14:00.790 --> 14:02.120
I know.

14:02.120 --> 14:03.670
Why didn't you
just return him?

14:03.670 --> 14:05.670
'Cause he's so sweet,
and if I brought him back,

14:05.670 --> 14:07.210
they'd just sell him to
someone else who'd eat him.

14:07.210 --> 14:09.080
Yeah.
Because he's food.

14:11.580 --> 14:13.290
What are you doing?
It's a complaint
bracelet.

14:13.290 --> 14:14.880
You snap it so you don't
tell your husband

14:14.880 --> 14:16.250
what an idiot he is.

14:16.250 --> 14:17.420
If I hadn't brought
a pig in this house,

14:17.420 --> 14:19.080
I'd have a real problem
with you wearing that.

14:19.080 --> 14:20.500
If the pig is in
our bedroom,

14:20.500 --> 14:22.380
then what are you cooking
in that box?

14:22.380 --> 14:24.380
Two briskets. I stopped by
the deli on the way home.

14:24.380 --> 14:25.710
I don't have time
for this right now.

14:25.710 --> 14:27.330
I have to give my presentation
to the Gala Board.

14:27.330 --> 14:28.620
Do you want to
rehearse with me?

14:28.620 --> 14:30.540
Nah, I got this.

14:30.540 --> 14:33.460
Are you sure? You're not
the greatest at winging it.

14:33.460 --> 14:35.250
You tried to wing our wedding
vows and wound up just

14:35.250 --> 14:36.920
repeating my vows back to me,
only adding a few

14:36.920 --> 14:38.170
"totally totally's."

14:38.170 --> 14:39.830
Like, I said,
"You are my sun and moon,"

14:39.830 --> 14:41.460
and when it was your
turn, you said,

14:41.460 --> 14:43.330
"You are totally totally
my sun and moon."

14:43.330 --> 14:45.710
Stop worrying about
my presentation.

14:45.710 --> 14:48.330
It's just three ding-aling moms
sitting around a lunch table.

14:48.330 --> 14:50.120
They'll hear
"beach blanket bingo"

14:50.120 --> 14:52.830
and be so happy that they'll
have to get emergency Botox

14:52.830 --> 14:53.830
to hide
their smile lines.

14:53.830 --> 14:56.790
Oh, my God!
We got a weird dog!

14:56.790 --> 15:00.170
[ Oinking ]
Hi. Hi, weird dog.

15:00.170 --> 15:07.790
♪♪

15:07.790 --> 15:09.580
Tara.
Katie.

15:09.580 --> 15:10.920
Of course you're on
the committee.

15:10.920 --> 15:12.750
No, I'm here for fun.

15:12.750 --> 15:14.830
I cleared my schedule
to watch you crash and burn

15:14.830 --> 15:15.750
from the audience.

15:15.750 --> 15:16.790
Audience?

15:16.790 --> 15:18.420
Mm-hmm.

15:22.880 --> 15:23.880
Pwooh.

15:25.880 --> 15:27.710
Katie: What is wrong
with these people?

15:27.710 --> 15:29.790
It is just a theme
for a dumb fundraiser.

15:29.790 --> 15:32.880
Don't freak out.
Think of something happy.

15:32.880 --> 15:35.880
God, that airbag hit Greg
in the face so hard.

15:35.880 --> 15:38.000
[ Chuckles ]

15:40.420 --> 15:45.620
Katie: Fun. Casual.
Picnic baskets...

15:45.620 --> 15:48.960
that pink wine...

15:48.960 --> 15:51.500
sitting on blankets...

15:51.500 --> 15:52.880
sand...

15:56.380 --> 15:58.670
macaroni salad...

16:04.540 --> 16:08.710
...is what Tara Summers
suggested we do.

16:08.710 --> 16:14.920
But I told Tara, "This is
a fundraiser, not a hoedown."

16:14.920 --> 16:17.170
Silly, stupid Tara.

16:18.790 --> 16:22.880
What I'm pitching, against
Tara's advice, is Bollywood!

16:22.880 --> 16:24.330
With more spectacle
and pageantry

16:24.330 --> 16:25.620
than you can even imagine.

16:25.620 --> 16:27.290
Yes. Yes!

16:27.290 --> 16:30.580
Picture the opulence of
a white chocolate Taj Mahal.

16:30.580 --> 16:34.040
Delicious food, all meat-based.

16:34.040 --> 16:37.960
And dancers with curvy swords
wearing gold M.C. Hammer pants.

16:37.960 --> 16:39.210
[ Laughs ]

16:39.210 --> 16:41.170
She knows what
I'm talkin' about!

16:41.170 --> 16:46.710
And, for our big finale,
we are going to have...

16:46.710 --> 16:48.250
[ Laughs nervously ]

16:48.250 --> 16:49.620
[Quietly]
What are we gonna have?

16:49.620 --> 16:50.830
[ Gasps ]

16:50.830 --> 16:52.290
[ Normal voice ]
Elephants!

16:52.290 --> 16:56.290
That's right, elephants
cloaked in velvet!

16:56.290 --> 16:58.620
And who's riding that elephant?

17:00.380 --> 17:02.830
Who, Katie? Who's riding
the elephant?

17:02.830 --> 17:06.330
Who's gonna get that lady
all excited?

17:06.330 --> 17:09.750
Nathan Fillion
from ABC's "Castle"!

17:11.290 --> 17:13.460
I love Castle!

17:13.460 --> 17:14.830
He's my Hall Pass.

17:14.830 --> 17:17.170
Yes!

17:17.170 --> 17:19.710
[ Applause ]

17:19.710 --> 17:26.710
♪♪

17:26.710 --> 17:29.540
♪♪

17:29.540 --> 17:33.620
[ Laughing ]

17:33.620 --> 17:35.290
I am so screwed.

17:35.290 --> 17:36.330
We tried to warn you.

17:36.330 --> 17:38.210
You know Nathan Fillion?

17:38.210 --> 17:40.620
Doris, you and I have talked
for at least 10,000 hours.

17:40.620 --> 17:42.460
Don't you think you'd know
if I knew Nathan Fillion?!

17:44.080 --> 17:45.210
That's for you.

17:45.210 --> 17:47.000
I'm not good
at winging it.

17:47.000 --> 17:49.250
I can't believe I'm saying this
to a man bottle-feeding a pig,

17:49.250 --> 17:51.000
but I should have
listened to you.

17:51.000 --> 17:52.830
But instead,
I listened to you.

17:52.830 --> 17:54.210
Why did I listen to you?

17:54.210 --> 17:56.210
We're not men,
we're Ottos!

17:56.210 --> 17:58.290
I should be with Alice
on her boat right now,

17:58.290 --> 18:00.250
sitting at the raw bar in my
just-the-right-amount-of-tight

18:00.250 --> 18:03.380
European-style swimsuit.

18:03.380 --> 18:04.960
You were right. I should
have let you stop me.

18:04.960 --> 18:07.960
No, you were right, too.
I shouldn't have winged it.

18:07.960 --> 18:09.540
It's just hard to know
when to say "okay"

18:09.540 --> 18:11.080
and when to stop
a dumb idea.

18:11.080 --> 18:13.000
So I guess we just have
to support one another,

18:13.000 --> 18:15.500
hope for the best, and deal
with the fallout together.

18:15.500 --> 18:17.040
Deal.

18:17.040 --> 18:18.580
Oh, good, I'm glad
you're agreeing, 'cause...

18:18.580 --> 18:20.500
while you were gone,
the pig chewed that

18:20.500 --> 18:23.380
Coach purse you picked up
at the school lost and found.

18:23.380 --> 18:25.710
I'm sawwy.

18:25.710 --> 18:27.250
I can't believe

18:27.250 --> 18:28.920
you humiliated me in front
of the Board of Directors.

18:28.920 --> 18:30.920
I can't believe you can't
believe I wouldn't do that.

18:30.920 --> 18:32.620
You know what?
It was worth it.

18:32.620 --> 18:33.920
Because there's no way that
you're gonna pull off

18:33.920 --> 18:35.920
even half of those promises.

18:35.920 --> 18:37.710
The Board will crucify you.

18:37.710 --> 18:38.710
And I'll be there to watch.

18:38.710 --> 18:39.830
[ R.J. oinks ]

18:39.830 --> 18:41.120
What is this?!

18:41.120 --> 18:42.790
A turkey.

18:43.920 --> 18:45.790
Eyo! We're leaving.

18:45.790 --> 18:47.210
Hey, Mom.

18:47.210 --> 18:48.880
Did you and Taylor
talk about college?

18:48.880 --> 18:50.620
We did.
And?

18:50.620 --> 18:53.290
And...

18:53.290 --> 18:56.120
I've decided I don't want
to be an anesthesiologist.

18:56.120 --> 18:58.080
What?

18:58.080 --> 18:59.710
I'm gonna study manga.

18:59.710 --> 19:01.880
What?!
Manga is my passion.

19:01.880 --> 19:05.460
No. Safely sedating a patient
before surgery is your passion!

19:05.460 --> 19:06.960
One afternoon
in this house

19:06.960 --> 19:10.250
and he wants to throw
his life away on doodles!

19:10.250 --> 19:12.290
Bye, Tara. See you never,
I hope.

19:12.290 --> 19:14.330
Not kidding.
Hey, you, get out.

19:14.330 --> 19:16.620
So, instead of him convincing
you to go to college,

19:16.620 --> 19:18.710
somehow you convinced him
not to go to college?

19:18.710 --> 19:21.170
I just supported him like you
guys have been talking about.

19:21.170 --> 19:23.420
You kids honestly picked
the worst time to listen to us.

19:23.420 --> 19:24.710
Yeah.

19:24.710 --> 19:27.290
♪♪

19:27.290 --> 19:28.790
Don't mind us! We'll store it
in the garage.

19:28.790 --> 19:31.120
Oh, good, dent the other door.
Even things out.

19:32.460 --> 19:34.880
Hup, that lamp needed
a good knocking-over.

19:34.880 --> 19:36.710
Oh, we cleared the piano.

19:40.540 --> 19:43.540
Oh, no! You broke the ceramic
owl your mother gave us.

19:43.540 --> 19:44.620
You did that on purpose.

19:44.620 --> 19:46.880
True, but you brought home
a live pig.

19:46.880 --> 19:48.040
How long are you gonna
play the pig card?

19:48.040 --> 19:49.210
How long does
a pig live?

19:49.210 --> 19:50.620
On average,
about 15 years.

19:50.620 --> 19:52.040
Oh, crap.

19:52.040 --> 19:55.500
♪♪

20:02.710 --> 20:04.750
Me and Hans Gruber
are going upstairs.

20:04.750 --> 20:06.330
I'm going to give
him a bath.

20:06.330 --> 20:08.330
You renamed the pig
Hans Gruber?

20:08.330 --> 20:10.210
Yeah. He tried to kill
Bruce Willis

20:10.210 --> 20:11.670
in my new favorite movie,
"Die Hard."

20:11.670 --> 20:12.880
You watched
"Die Hard"?

20:12.880 --> 20:14.500
Yeah, with Mama.

20:14.500 --> 20:17.120
Sweetie,
what is the rule

20:17.120 --> 20:19.670
about Mama/Anna-Kat
movie time?

20:19.670 --> 20:22.080
"If Daddy asks, we always
watched 'Despicable Me.'"

20:23.880 --> 20:25.170
Oh, right.

20:25.170 --> 20:26.540
Hans Gruber's
a minion.

20:30.580 --> 20:32.750
[ Snap ]

20:32.750 --> 20:36.880
In my defense, you weren't
supposed to find out about it.

20:36.880 --> 20:39.170
It's a good defense.

20:39.170 --> 20:42.670
♪♪
